# Tasks: Eval/JIT Compile System

**Input**: Design documents from `/specs/017-eval-jit-compile/`
**Prerequisites**: plan.md, spec.md, research.md, data-model.md, contracts/

**Tests**: Included per Constitution Principle VII (TDD - éžäº¤æ¸‰)

**Organization**: Tasks grouped by user story for independent implementation and testing.

## Format: `[ID] [P?] [Story?] Description`

- **[P]**: Can run in parallel (different files, no dependencies)
- **[Story]**: Which user story (US1, US2, US3, US4, US5)
- Exact file paths included

## Path Conventions

- **Source**: `src/clysm/eval/` (existing module)
- **Tests**: `tests/unit/`, `tests/integration/`, `tests/contract/`

---

## Phase 1: Setup (Package Exports)

**Purpose**: Ensure package exports are complete for new functionality

- [ ] T001 Add tiered-function exports to src/clysm/package.lisp
- [ ] T002 [P] Add compile test package definition to tests/package.lisp

---

## Phase 2: Foundational (Data Structures)

**Purpose**: Core data structures that ALL user stories depend on

**âš ï¸ CRITICAL**: Must complete before any user story implementation

- [ ] T003 Define tiered-function struct in src/clysm/eval/compile.lisp
- [ ] T004 [P] Define tiered-function-wrapper macro in src/clysm/eval/compile.lisp
- [ ] T005 [P] Add reset-invocation-counts utility for testing in src/clysm/eval/compile.lisp
- [ ] T006 Add reset-function-slots utility for testing in src/clysm/eval/jit.lisp

**Checkpoint**: Foundation ready - tiered-function struct and utilities available

---

## Phase 3: User Story 1 - Compile Anonymous Lambda (Priority: P1) ðŸŽ¯ MVP

**Goal**: `(compile nil '(lambda (x) (+ x 1)))` returns a callable function

**Independent Test**: Call `(compile* nil '(lambda (x) (+ x 1)))`, invoke result with 5, verify returns 6

### Tests for User Story 1

> **TDD: Write tests FIRST, ensure they FAIL before implementation**

- [ ] T007 [P] [US1] Unit test for compile* with nil name in tests/unit/compile-test.lisp
- [ ] T008 [P] [US1] Unit test for compile* with single-param lambda in tests/unit/compile-test.lisp
- [ ] T009 [P] [US1] Unit test for compile* with multi-param lambda in tests/unit/compile-test.lisp
- [ ] T010 [P] [US1] Unit test for compile* with zero-param lambda in tests/unit/compile-test.lisp
- [ ] T011 [P] [US1] Unit test for compile* error on non-lambda in tests/unit/compile-test.lisp
- [ ] T012 [US1] Integration test for anonymous lambda compilation in tests/integration/compile-test.lisp

### Implementation for User Story 1

- [ ] T013 [US1] Implement validate-lambda-expr in src/clysm/eval/compile.lisp

- [ ] T015 [US1] Implement make-tiered-wrapper function in src/clysm/eval/compile.lisp
- [ ] T016 [US1] Verify compile* returns callable function for all lambda forms

**Checkpoint**: `(compile nil '(lambda ...))` works, returns callable function

---

## Phase 4: User Story 2 - Tier 1 Interpreted Execution (Priority: P1)

**Goal**: Newly compiled functions execute through Tier 1 interpreter by default

**Independent Test**: Compile a function, call it <10 times, verify executed through interpreter

### Tests for User Story 2

- [ ] T017 [P] [US2] Unit test: new function starts at :tier-1 in tests/unit/compile-test.lisp
- [ ] T018 [P] [US2] Unit test: function below threshold stays in Tier 1 in tests/unit/compile-test.lisp
- [ ] T019 [P] [US2] Integration test for all special forms via Tier 1 in tests/integration/compile-test.lisp

### Implementation for User Story 2

- [ ] T020 [US2] Ensure tiered-function initializes with tier=:tier-1 in src/clysm/eval/compile.lisp
- [ ] T021 [US2] Verify interpreter handles all special forms (if, let, let*, lambda, progn, setq, block, return-from, tagbody, go, flet, labels) in src/clysm/eval/interpreter.lisp
- [ ] T022 [US2] Add tier accessor function get-current-tier in src/clysm/eval/compile.lisp

**Checkpoint**: Tier 1 execution verified for all special forms

---

## Phase 5: User Story 3 - Automatic Tier Promotion (Priority: P2)

**Goal**: Functions exceeding threshold (default 10) automatically promote to Tier 2

**Independent Test**: Call function 11 times, verify tier changes from :tier-1 to :tier-2

### Tests for User Story 3

- [ ] T026 [P] [US3] Contract test: promotion produces valid Wasm in tests/contract/tier-promotion-test.lisp
- [ ] T027 [US3] Integration test for automatic tier promotion in tests/integration/tier-promotion-test.lisp

### Implementation for User Story 3

- [ ] T028 [US3] Implement invocation counting in tiered-wrapper in src/clysm/eval/compile.lisp
- [ ] T029 [US3] Implement threshold check in wrapper invocation in src/clysm/eval/compile.lisp
- [ ] T030 [US3] Implement attempt-tier-promotion with graceful degradation in src/clysm/eval/compile.lisp
- [ ] T031 [US3] Update tiered-function tier slot on successful promotion in src/clysm/eval/compile.lisp
- [ ] T032 [US3] Implement promotion-failed-p tracking to avoid retry in src/clysm/eval/compile.lisp

**Checkpoint**: Hot spot detection and automatic promotion working

---

## Phase 6: User Story 4 - Compile Named Functions (Priority: P2)

**Goal**: `(compile 'my-fn '(lambda ...))` registers function in symbol's function slot

**Independent Test**: Compile named function, lookup via function slot, verify callable

### Tests for User Story 4

- [ ] T033 [P] [US4] Unit test: named compile registers in *function-slots* in tests/unit/compile-test.lisp
- [ ] T034 [P] [US4] Unit test: get-function-slot retrieves registered function in tests/unit/compile-test.lisp

- [ ] T036 [US4] Integration test for named function compile and call in tests/integration/compile-test.lisp

- [ ] T038 [US4] Ensure hot-patch updates both function slot and tiered-function in src/clysm/eval/compile.lisp
- [ ] T039 [US4] Add lookup-compiled-function utility in src/clysm/eval/compile.lisp

**Checkpoint**: Named function compilation and hot-patching working

---

## Phase 7: User Story 5 - Dynamic Module Linking (Priority: P3)

**Goal**: JIT-compiled Wasm modules link to runtime imports at instantiation

**Independent Test**: JIT-compile function using cons/car/cdr, verify correct execution

### Tests for User Story 5

- [ ] T042 [P] [US5] Contract test: JIT module receives imports in tests/contract/module-linking-test.lisp
- [ ] T043 [US5] Integration test for JIT function calling runtime import in tests/integration/jit-test.lisp

### Implementation for User Story 5

- [ ] T044 [US5] Enhance instantiate-wasm to bind runtime imports in src/clysm/eval/jit.lisp
- [ ] T045 [US5] Add missing runtime imports (append, length, etc.) in src/clysm/eval/jit.lisp
- [ ] T046 [US5] Implement import resolution for JIT-compiled modules in src/clysm/eval/jit.lisp

**Checkpoint**: JIT modules correctly link to runtime imports

---

## Phase 8: Polish & Cross-Cutting Concerns

**Purpose**: Integration, error handling, and validation

- [ ] T047 [P] Add edge case test: compile invalid syntax in tests/unit/compile-test.lisp
- [ ] T048 [P] Add edge case test: closure environment capture in tests/integration/compile-test.lisp
- [ ] T049 [P] Add edge case test: Tier 2 compilation failure graceful degradation in tests/integration/tier-promotion-test.lisp
- [ ] T050 [P] Add edge case test: recursive function tier promotion in tests/integration/tier-promotion-test.lisp
- [ ] T051 [P] Add edge case test: hot-patch during execution in tests/integration/compile-test.lisp
- [ ] T052 Verify all tests pass via nix flake check
- [ ] T053 Run quickstart.md validation examples
- [ ] T054 Update CLAUDE.md with feature completion status

---

## Dependencies & Execution Order

### Phase Dependencies
